{
  "texts": [
    "In this case, authors either rephrased items or generated entirely new test stimuli.",
    "Although modified tests may reduce the probability of LLMs having seen items before testing, evidence that such changes are still valid for the intended use is required.",
    "We acknowledged such evidence in only one study: Coda-Forno et al. (2023) compare the answers on rephrased and original test items and find a significant correlation, as well as no significant difference in the final test score.",
    "R5a (Test Validity for all Models) When assessing multiple LLMs, requirement R5a demands proof of validity for each tested model.",
    "Out of the affected ten studies, only a single provides a thorough analysis in this regard (Serapio-García et al., 2023)."
  ]
}